gress-steps#features","content":"Interactive (navigable) and inert (display-only) steps"},"662":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-22","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#features","content":"Title truncation and RTL support"},"663":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-23","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#features","content":"Rendered as a `<nav>` landmark with an ordered list for assistive technology"},"664":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-24","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#props","content":"`ProgressSteps` is the container; its direct children must be `ProgressStep` elements."},"665":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-25","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#default","content":"A horizontal stepper. `currentStep` marks the active step; earlier steps are `past`, later are `future`. Each `status` sets the step's icon, and an `error` step turns its accent bar red."},"666":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-26","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#not-started","content":"Omit `currentStep` for a flow that hasn't begun: every step is `future` and none is marked current."},"667":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-27","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#vertical","content":"Use `orientation=\"vertical\"` to place the accent bar on the leading edge and stack steps in a column."},"668":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-28","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#interactive","content":"Give a step an `onPress` handler to make it navigable. Steps without 