/progress-steps#best-practices","content":"Provide `onPress` only for steps a user can actually navigate to; leave it off for display-only steps."},"683":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-43","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#best-practices","content":"Keep titles short — they truncate with an ellipsis when space is tight."},"684":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-44","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#best-practices","content":"Always give the container an `aria-label` that describes the flow (e.g. `\"Checkout progress\"`)."},"685":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-45","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#troubleshooting","content":"**No step is highlighted:** `currentStep` is omitted, negative, or out of range. Set it to the active step's 0-based index."},"686":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-46","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#troubleshooting","content":"**A step isn't clickable:** it has no `onPress`, so it's inert by design. Add `onPress` to make it interactive."},"687":{"id":"/docs/components/progress-steps-47","page_id":"/docs/components/progress-steps","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/progress-steps#troubleshooting","content":"**Titles overflow:** that's expected — titles truncate. Shorten the title."},"688":{"id":"/docs/components/radio","page_id":"/docs/components/radio","type":"page","content":"Radio","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/radio"},"689":{"id":"/docs/components/radio-0","page_id":"/docs/components/radio","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/radio","content":"Accessible radio button component for mutually exclusive selections with keyboard navigation, validation states, and flex