/chart/bar-chart#performance-issues","content":"**Simplify tooltips**: If tooltips are complex, consider using simpler content or disabling them"},"1177":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-179","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"All examples can be found in the Storybook interface:"},"1178":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-180","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"**Single Series**: Basic vertical bar chart"},"1179":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-181","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"**Multi-Series**: Grouped bars with legend"},"1180":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-182","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"**Horizontal Single Series**: Horizontal orientation"},"1181":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-183","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"**Horizontal Multi-Series**: Grouped horizontal bars"},"1182":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-184","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"**Custom Domain**: Controlled x and y ranges"},"1183":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart-185","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/bar-chart#examples","content":"**RTL Multi-Series*&#x2A;: Multi-series chart in RTL &#x2A;(in development)*"},"1184":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"page","content":"DonutChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart"},"1185":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","content":"Donut charts are for parts-to-whole comparison—how partial elements add up to a total—shown as a ring so a few categories are easy to compare at a glance."},"1186":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#installation","content":"Installation"},"1187":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#props","content":"Props"},"1188":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1189":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#basic","content":"Basic"},"1190":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#single-slice","content":"Single slice"},"1191":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Legend placement"},"1192":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Small slices"},"1193":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Format value"},"1194":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-9","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#basic","content":"You give the chart a `data` array (`id`, `name`, `value`) and a `label` in the middle—this is the everyday setup when you want several categories on one ring and a headline number or title in the hole."},"1195":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-10","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#single-slice","content":"When there is only one slice, the ring is full. Add `subLabel` if you want a smaller second line under the main center text."},"1196":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Switch `legend` to `right` to sit the legend beside the donut, or `bottom` to stack it underneath. `legendLabel` is there when you want a title above the legend items."},"1197":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Very thin slices can be noisy to hover. Anything at or below `smallSliceThreshold` (default `0.05` of the total) is treated as “small,” and if those slices sit next to each other on the ring, one hover opens a single tooltip that lists the whole group."},"1198":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Use `formatValue` when the raw numbers in the tooltip should read like money, counts with separators, or whatever your product expects. The percentage of the total still formats on its own; your function only shapes the value column."},"1199":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/gauge-chart","